===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|butcher||}}

# To slaughter animals and prepare meat for [[market]].
# To kill brutally.
# To ruin something, often to the point of defamation.
#: ''The band at that bar really '''butchered''' "Hotel California".''

